#: ../../user-manual/add-edit-content/authority-records.rst:586
msgid ""
"In AtoM, access points are controlled value :term:`terms <term>` maintained "
"in a :term:`taxonomy`, which can be used to aid in discovery. With the 2.5 "
"release, AtoM supports three types of access points for authority records - "
"Occupations, Places, and Subjects. By default in a new installation, the "
"related taxonomy is empty, but as users add access point data to authority "
"records, they are preserved as terms in the Actor occupation, Places, and "
"Subjects taxonomies, so they can be managed and reused. For more information"
" on working with terms and taxonomies in AtoM, see: :ref:`terms`."
msgstr ""
